      "writtenOn": "2020-07-22T20:54:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m fine with renaming it if you want, but FWIW I am not sure that matching the name on GrPaint is necessarily a useful quality. If you look at how the GrPipeline is assembled: https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/master:third_party/skia/src/gpu/GrPipeline.cpp;l\u003d51\n\n... it combines the `coverage` from the GrPaint and the `clipCoverage` from the GrAppliedClip. I was just taking in that code for the first time today, and to me this separation in names provided a useful distinction. But I don\u0027t feel strongly about it at all.",
      "parentUuid": "a6d4c75d_99be7494",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 108,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 108,
        "endChar": 40
      },
